# GitHub Actions — path-filtered Cloudflare deploy

When adding or editing workflows that **deploy** to Cloudflare **Pages** or **Workers**, follow these rules. Binding names and Wrangler file layout stay in **`40-cloudflare-wrangler.mdc`**.

## One deploy target per workflow file

- Each workflow run should call **`wrangler pages deploy`** at most **once** with **one** `--project-name`, or **`wrangler deploy`** for **one** Worker root / config.
- Do **not** use a single workflow that builds and deploys every app under `apps/**` or every service under `services/**` when only one product changed.

## Path triggers (`on.push` / `pull_request`)

Include **only** paths that should trigger this deploy:

1. **App or service root** — e.g. `apps/my-app/**`, `services/my-api/**`.
2. **Workspace packages that app imports** — list explicit globs like `packages/ui/**`, not blanket `packages/**`, unless every package truly affects the bundle (then document why).
3. **Repo roots that affect install/build** — `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, root `package.json`, `.nvmrc` when present.
4. **This workflow file** — e.g. `.github/workflows/deploy-pages-my-app.yml` so CI edits re-run the workflow.

Also add **`workflow_dispatch`** so operators can redeploy without a matching path change.

## Anti-patterns

- **`paths: ['apps/**']`** plus **`pnpm --filter "./apps/*"`** — any app change rebuilds or deploy targets for all apps; split per app or use `dorny/paths-filter` + conditional jobs.
- **`packages/**` on a single-app workflow** when only a few workspace packages are linked — widens triggers; list **only** imported `packages/*` trees.

## Concurrency

Use **`concurrency.group`** scoped to the deploy target (e.g. `deploy-pages-docs-app`) so two pushes do not corrupt the same Worker/Pages upload.

## Preflight (required)

Before any step that runs `wrangler deploy` or provisions Cloudflare resources, add:

```yaml
- name: Cloudflare preflight
  run: node scripts/preflight-cloudflare.mjs
  env:
    CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.CF_API_TOKEN }}
    CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID: ${{ secrets.CF_ACCOUNT_ID }}
    CF_WORKERS_SUBDOMAIN: ${{ vars.CF_WORKERS_SUBDOMAIN }}
```

See **`15-org-account-isolation.mdc`**. Never deploy from a developer laptop to production.

## Optional consolidation

- **`dorny/paths-filter`** — one workflow, multiple outputs, `if:` per job to deploy only changed apps (fewer YAML files, more YAML logic).
- **Pages connected to Git** — align Cloudflare **Watch paths** with the same globs as Actions `paths`.

